This paper is primarily focused on the performance of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) on randomized image data, which is a common problem in computer vision (CV) tasks. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of the randomization process on the classification accuracy of CNNs, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of dilated convolutions to recover some of the pixel correlations, which is a technique commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
